  "description": "Production of semiconductor-grade ultra-pure water (18.2 MΩ·cm), 9N+ (99.9999999%) purity chemicals, and ppt-level analytical verification. Standard industrial chemistry produces 95-99.5% purity — this domain covers the 6-7 order of magnitude purity leap required for wafer processing. Multi-stage purification (sub-boiling distillation, RO, electrodeionization, UV oxidation) and contamination detection (ICP-MS, TOC analysis, particle counting) at parts-per-trillion levels.",
